==Reactions==
Hugo Chavez mentioned an episode of the series to Evo Morales in 2011, with [[ABC News]] quoting him: "You've got to see this show, Evo!" Chávez boomed to his staff, laughing about how Morales was left snoring while "Hugito" sang until sun-up. "They sound just like us!"<ref>{{cite web|last1=News|first1=A. B. C.|title=Venezuelan Comedians Seek Life After Chavez|url=http://abcnews.go.com/ABC_Univision/News/venezuelan-comedians-seek-life-chavez/story?id=18766359|website=ABC News|date=19 March 2013}}</ref>

[[Nicolás Maduro]], president of Venezuela, was portrayed as a man of limited intelligence, twisted speech, and capable of talking with birds. This is a reference to a comment made by Maduro during the 2013 elections in Venezuela, when he said that the late Chávez had reincarnated in a little bird and talked to him to bless his candidacy.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/mundo/Maduro-pajarito-llegan-Isla-Presidencial_0_977902438.html|title= Maduro y su pajarito llegan a "La Isla Presidencial"|trans-title=Maduro and his bird arrive on "La Isla Presidencial"|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 20, 2013|work= |publisher= Clarín|accessdate=February 3, 2014}}</ref> Maduro criticized his portrayal in the animation. He said that it was not an accurate representation of his face, his moustache, of his voice.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://cnnchile.com/noticia/2013/08/19/nicolas-maduro-hablo-sobre-su-llegada-a-isla-presidencial|title= Nicolás Maduro habló sobre su llegada a Isla Presidencial|trans-title=Nicolás Maduro spoke about his arrival to Isla Presidencial|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 19, 2013|work= |publisher= CNN Chile|accessdate=February 3, 2014}}</ref>

