'''Mari Albert Johan van Manen''' ([[Nijmegen]], 16 April 1877 – [[Kolkata]], 17 March 1943) was a [[Dutch people|Dutch]] [[oriental studies|orientalist]] and the first Dutch [[Tibetology|Tibetologist]]. A large portion of his collected manuscripts and art and [[ethnographic]] projects now make up the Van Manen collection at [[Leiden University]]'s Kern Institute.<ref>{{cite web|author=Yang Enhong |url=http://www.iias.nl/iiasn/19/regions/c1.html |title=Johan van Manen: The founder of Tibetology in the Netherlands |publisher=International Institute for Asian Studies |date= |accessdate=24 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://dutchstudies-satsea.nl/auteur/85/MariAlbertJohanvan-Manen.html |title=Mari Albert Johan van Manen |publisher=Dutch Studies on South Asia, Tibet and classical Southeast Asia |date= |accessdate=24 January 2016}}</ref>

